The paper deals with combinatorial and information-theoretic properties of Sturmian words, which are a well-studied topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of the square root map is related to the factor complexity of Sturmian words, which is a topic in formal languages (cs.FL) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of fixed points and equations in Sturmian words, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and symbolic dynamics (cs.SI).
